            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "You usually use the reloader during development so you don't need a manual restart. Also, a decorator makes not much sense for this. The Python code quality is also pretty low. Import should not be local, `commands.getoutput` most likely  uses a shell instead of an argv-style list and calling `kill` from Python makes no sense since Python has `os.kill()` for this.\n\nAll in all, this belongs not in Flask. Why not do something like this locally if you need it?\n"
